  "prompt": "Re the Sochi Olympics online video coverage, if I want to watch an event on streaming video but I cannot watch it live, is there some kind of archive after the event first airs?",
  "response": "Yes, for the Sochi Olympics, many broadcasters and streaming platforms provided archives of events so viewers could watch them after the live broadcast. Here\u2019s how it typically worked:\n\n1. **Official Broadcasters**: Networks like NBC (in the U.S.), BBC (in the U.K.), and others often uploaded full event replays to their websites or apps shortly after the events concluded. These archives were usually accessible for a limited time.\n\n2. **Streaming Platforms**: Platforms like the NBC Sports App, BBC iPlayer, or the official Olympic Channel often had on-demand sections where viewers could watch replays of events.\n\n3. **Subscription Services**: Some services, like Peacock (NBC\u2019s streaming platform), may have archived Olympic content available for subscribers even after the Games ended.\n\nTo access archived coverage, you\u2019d need to check the specific platform or broadcaster that held the rights in your region. Note that availability might vary depending on the platform and region, and some archives may no longer be accessible after the Games concluded for copyright or licensing reasons. If you're looking for Sochi content now, you might also find highlights on YouTube or other video-sharing platforms.",
